      • searchImageInfoURL

        public static java.net.URL searchImageInfoURL(org.openstreetmap.josm.data.Bounds bounds,
                                              int page,
                                              MapillaryURL.IMAGE_SELECTOR selector)
        Gives you the API-URL where you get 20 images within the given bounds. For more than 20 images you have to use different URLs with different page numbers.
        Parameters:
        bounds - the bounds in which you want to search for images
        page - number of the page to retrieve from the API
        selector - if set, only a specific type of image is returned by the URL
        Returns:
        the API-URL which gives you the images in the given bounds as JSON

      • searchSequenceURL

        public static java.net.URL searchSequenceURL(org.openstreetmap.josm.data.Bounds bounds,
                                             int page)
        Gives you the API-URL where you get 10 sequences within the given bounds. For more than 10 sequences you have to use different URLs with different page numbers.
        Parameters:
        bounds - the bounds in which you want to search for sequences
        page - number of the page to retrieve from the API
        Returns:
        the API-URL which gives you the sequences in the given bounds as JSON
